cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with generating adversarial text sequences to evade deep learning classifiers, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. As the paper deals with security and attacks on deep learning models, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, as the paper involves text data, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
